Dr. Magnus' Background






Bio


Robert E. Magnus, MD is a practicing Orthopedic Surgeon in Dubuque, IA. Dr. Magnus graduated from University of Chicago Division of the Biological Sciences the Pritzker School of Medicine in 1986 and has been in practice for 31 years. He completed a residency at Sinai Grace Hospital. He currently practices at Medical Associates Clinic and is affiliated with Mercy Medical Center Dubuque, Genesis Medical Center West Campus and Hammond-Henry Hospital. Dr. Magnus accepts multiple insurance plans including Wellmark, Medicare and Cigna. Dr. Magnus is board certified in Orthopaedic Surgery. In addition to English, Dr. Magnus's practice supports these languages: Spanish and French. Displaying the profile of a physician or provider on this website does not constitute or imply endorsement, recommendation, or favoring by the sponsoring hospital. The views and opinions of authors expressed herein do not necessarily state or reflect those of Trinity Health Corporation or any of its hospitals/ministries, and shall not be used for advertising or product endorsement purposes.





